Non-functional requirements define the quality attributes and performance standards of the Smart Queue Management System for Banks.
NFR-01: Performance
The system shall respond to user actions such as token generation and queue updates within acceptable time limits.
•	Acceptance Criteria:
o	Token generation response time ≤ 2 seconds
o	Queue status updates occur in near real time
NFR-02: Security
The system shall ensure secure access and protect user data.
•	Acceptance Criteria:
o	Role-based login for staff and admin
o	Unauthorized access is prevented
NFR-03: Reliability & Availability
The system shall be available during bank working hours with minimal downtime.
•	Acceptance Criteria:
o	System availability of at least 99%
o	Automatic recovery from minor failures
NFR-04: Usability
The system shall be easy to use by customers and bank staff.
•	Acceptance Criteria:
o	Simple and intuitive user interface
